vertices.label: China
vertices.description: cultural region, ancient civilization, and nation in East Asia, mostly refer to the People's Republic of China in political situation and rarely refer to the Republic of China

vertices.label: soybean
vertices.description: species of plant in the Fabaceae family

vertices.label: National Inventory of Intangible Cultural Heritage in Malaysia
vertices.description: national inventory of intangible cultural heritage in Malaysia

vertices.label: tofu
vertices.description: soy-based food used as a protein source

properties.label: cuisine
properties.description: type of food served by a restaurant or restaurant chain or national food culture

properties.label: by-product
properties.description: product of a chemical or industrial process, of secondary economic value

properties.label: intangible cultural heritage status
properties.description: status of an item that is designated as intangible heritage

properties.label: subclass of
properties.description: this item is a subclass (subset) of that item; all instances of this item are instances of that item; different from P31 (instance of), e.g.: volcano is a subclass of mountain (and an instance of volcanic landform); K2 is an instance of mountain

properties.label: has part(s)
properties.description: part of this subject; inverse property of "part of" (P361). See also "has parts of the class" (P2670).

properties.label: country of origin
properties.description: country of origin of this item (creative work, food, phrase, product, etc.)

properties.label: made from material
properties.description: material the subject or the object is made of or derived from (do not confuse with P10672 which is used for processes)

properties.label: instance of
properties.description: that class of which this subject is a particular example and member; different from P279 (subclass of); for example: K2 is an instance of mountain; volcano is a subclass of mountain (and an instance of volcanic landform)

properties.label: inception
properties.description: time when an entity begins to exist; for date of official opening use P1619
